quran[75]{c,v,t}:
  87,1,"Glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most High"
  87,2,"Who has created (everything), and then proportioned it"
  87,3,"And Who has measured (preordainments for each and everything even to be blessed or wretched); then guided (i.e. showed mankind the right as well as wrong paths, and guided the animals to pasture)"
  87,4,And Who brings out the pasturage
  87,5,And then makes it dark stubble
  87,6,"We shall make you to recite (the Quran), so you (O Muhammad (Peace be upon him)) shall not forget (it)"
  87,7,"Except what Allah, may will, He knows what is apparent and what is hidden"
  87,8,And We shall make easy for you (O Muhammad (Peace be upon him)) the easy way (i.e. the doing of righteous deeds)
  87,9,Therefore remind (men) in case the reminder profits (them)
  87,10,The reminder will be received by him who fears (Allah)
  87,11,But it will be avoided by the wretched
  87,12,Who will enter the great Fire and made to taste its burning
  87,13,Wherein he will neither die (to be in rest) nor live (a good living)
  87,14,Indeed whosoever purifies himself (by avoiding polytheism and accepting Islamic Monotheism) shall achieve success
  87,15,"And remembers (glorifies) the Name of his Lord (worships none but Allah), and prays (five compulsory prayers and Nawafil additional prayers)"
  87,16,"Nay, you prefer the life of this world"
  87,17,Although the Hereafter is better and more lasting
  87,18,Verily! This is in the former Scriptures
  87,19,The Scriptures of Ibrahim (Abraham) and Musa (Moses)
  88,1,Has there come to you the narration of the overwhelming (i.e. the Day of Resurrection)
  88,2,"Some faces, that Day, will be humiliated (in the Hell-fire, i.e. the faces of all disbelievers, Jews and Christians, etc)"
  88,3,"Labouring (hard in the worldly life by worshipping others besides Allah), weary (in the Hereafter with humility and disgrace)"
  88,4,They will enter in the hot blazing Fire
  88,5,They will be given to drink from a boiling spring
  88,6,No food will there be for them but a poisonous thorny plant
  88,7,Which will neither nourish nor avail against hunger
  88,8,"(Other) faces, that Day, will be joyful"
  88,9,"Glad with their endeavour (for their good deeds which they did in this world, along with the true Faith of Islamic Monotheism)"
  88,10,In a lofty Paradise
  88,11,Where they shall neither hear harmful speech nor falsehood
  88,12,Therein will be a running spring
  88,13,Therein will be thrones raised high
  88,14,And cups set at hand
  88,15,And cushions set in rows
  88,16,And rich carpets (all) spread out
  88,17,"Do they not look at the camels, how they are created"
  88,18,"And at the heaven, how it is raised"
  88,19,"And at the mountains, how they are rooted and fixed firm"
  88,20,"And at the earth, how it is spread out"
  88,21,"So remind them (O Muhammad (Peace be upon him)), you are only a one who reminds"
  88,22,You are not a dictator over them
  88,23,Save the one who turns away and disbelieves
  88,24,Then Allah will punish him with the greatest punishment
  88,25,"Verily, to Us will be their return"
  88,26,"Then verily, for Us will be their reckoning"
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,By the ten nights (i.e. the first ten days of the month of Dhul-Hijjah)
  89,3,And by the even and the odd (of all the creations of Allah)
  89,4,And by the night when it departs
  89,5,"There is indeed in them (the above oaths) sufficient proofs for men of understanding (and that, they should avoid all kinds of sins and disbeliefs, etc)"
  89,6,Did you (O Muhammad (Peace be upon him)) not see (thought) how your Lord dealt with 'Ad (people)
  89,7,Who were very tall like lofty pillars
  89,8,The like of which were not created in the land
  89,9,"And (with) Thamud (people), who cut (hewed) out rocks in the valley (to make dwellings)"
  89,10,"And (with) Fir'aun (Pharaoh), who had pegs (who used to torture men by binding them to pegs)"
  89,11,Who did transgress beyond bounds in the lands (in the disobedience of Allah)
  89,12,And made therein much mischief
  89,13,So your Lord poured on them different kinds of severe torment
  89,14,"Verily, your Lord is Ever Watchful (over them)"
  89,15,"As for man, when his Lord tries him by giving him honour and gifts, then he says (puffed up): \"My Lord has honoured me"
  89,16,"But when He tries him, by straitening his means of life, he says: \"My Lord has humiliated me"
  89,17,"Nay! But you treat not the orphans with kindness and generosity (i.e. you neither treat them well, nor give them their exact right of inheritance)"
  89,18,And urge not on the feeding of AlMiskin (the poor)
  89,19,And you devour inheritance all with greed
  89,20,And you love wealth with much love
  89,21,Nay! When the earth is ground to powder
  89,22,And your Lord comes with the angels in rows
  89,23,"And Hell will be brought near that Day. On that Day will man remember, but how will that remembrance (then) avail him"
  89,24,"He will say: \"Alas! Would that I had sent forth (good deeds) for (this) my life"
  89,25,"So on that Day, none will punish as He will punish"
  89,26,And none will bind as He will bind
  89,27,"(It will be said to the pious): \"O (you) the one in (complete) rest and satisfaction"
  89,28,"Come back to your Lord, Well-pleased (yourself) and well-pleasing unto Him"
  89,29,"Enter you, then, among My honoured slaves"
  89,30,And enter you My Paradise